        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 6:00PM EDT by NWS Tallahassee FL</headline>
        <description>At 559 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northwest of Perry. The strong thunderstorm is nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Perry, Lake Bird, Iddo, Ebb, Secotan, Boyd, Eridu, Sirmans, and Shady
Grove.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
